## 
##  Ljung-Box test
## 
## data:  Residuals from Regression with ARIMA(4,0,0)(1,1,2)[12] errors
## Q* = 18.331, df = 17, p-value = 0.3682
## 
## Model df: 7.   Total lags used: 24
library(forecast)

# Define the range of parameter values to search over
p_values <- c(0:4)    # Values for p
d_values <- c(0:1)    # Values for d
q_values <- c(0:2)    # Values for q
P_values <- c(0:1)    # Values for P (seasonal order)
D_values <- 1    # Values for D (seasonal difference)
Q_values <- c(0:2)    # Values for Q (seasonal MA order)
s_value <- 12         # Seasonal period

# Initialize an empty dataframe to store the results
results <- data.frame(p = integer(),
                      d = integer(),
                      q = integer(),
                      P = integer(),
                      D = integer(),
                      Q = integer(),
                      AICc = numeric())

# Loop over parameter combinations
for (p in p_values) {
  for (d in d_values) {
    for (q in q_values) {
      for (P in P_values) {
        for (D in D_values) {
          for (Q in Q_values) {
            # Fit the ARIMA model with current parameter values and covariate
            model <- Arima(log_import, xreg = log_export, order = c(p, d, q), seasonal = list(order = c(P, D, Q), period = s_value))
            
            # Calculate AICc
            AICc <- model$aicc
            
            # Store the results in the dataframe
            results <- rbind(results, c(p, d, q, P, D, Q, AICc))
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

# Rename the columns in the dataframe
colnames(results) <- c("p", "d", "q", "P", "D", "Q", "AICc")

# Sort the dataframe based on AICc in ascending order
results <- results[order(results$AICc), ]

# Print the top 10 models
top_10 <- head(results, 10)
print(top_10)

Forecast

export_fcast <- snaive(log_export, h = 12)
autoplot(export_fcast)

import_fcast2 <- forecast(arima_fit2, h = 12, xreg = (export_fcast$mean))
autoplot(import_fcast2)

# reverse transformation of forecasted values
import_fcast2$mean <- exp(import_fcast2$mean)
import_fcast2$lower <- exp(import_fcast2$lower)
import_fcast2$upper <- exp(import_fcast2$upper)

# reverse transformation of test set
import.test <- test[,2]

# rescale the historical data
import.hist <- exp(log_import)

accuracy(import_fcast2, import.test)
